<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/373: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at São Paulo</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CCR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cameron</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">São Paulo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-20T19:00:00-03:00">September
                                    20, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 20—5:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Manager of the Emprez at [<hi rend="italic">Emprezas?</hi>] Electricas
                            telephoned from Campinas that city bombed again this afternoon for the
                            fourth time, one bomb dropping in the repair shops of the Emprez at [<hi rend="italic">Emprezas?</hi>] Electricas situated half a mile from
                            the railway station wounding one workman damaging property.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CCR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cameron</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>